In fact, the same EFSA, in the scientific opinion of 2014, identifies:


   •

as many as seven possible ways of entering 
    Xc through imports of plants or parts of plants for commercial or ornamental purposes, destined for their planting;



   •

some sources of risk linked to the careless behavior of tourists who are poorly informed about the health problems of plants and to the lack of awareness of amateur nurserymen;


   •

hopes for the “ornamental plants of Rutaceae”, the ban on the import of plants or parts of plants for their planting for commercial uses, even if not yet applicable to all Rutaceae;


   •

in quarantine facilities, before and after entry, a possible way to contain the spread of the infection, with variable intensity depending on the size of the shipments.
